# Testing Overview
- Three users participated in prototype testing of the student health tracker System
- The goal was to evluate usability and user experience, focusing on core tasks such as logging in,recording health, and veiwing progress.

# Testing Process
- Each user asked to complete the main actions without prior instructions.
- observation were made on ease of navigation, clarity of interface, and ability to complete tasks.

# Results 
- All users successfully logged in, recorded health data, and veiwed progress.
- Minor hesitation ocuurred when locating the activity recording section, but users adapted quickly.
- Dashboard layout, icons, and progress indicators wrer consistently praised for clarity and usability.

# Insights and Improvements
- The system is generally intuitive and user-friendly
- Improvemnets needed: make the activity recording section more visible, refine navigation for first time users.
- Feedback confirmed that the prototype supports the projects goal of promoting student health tracking.

# Conclusion
The user testing confirmed that the prototype meets its primary usability goals. Small refinements will further enchance 
the overall user experience.
